        "title": "Fix one-shot Codex app-server teardown",
        "body": "## Summary\n- forwards one-shot cleanup flags through gateway agent requests into embedded Codex attempts\n- retires and closes the shared Codex app-server client at the start of one-shot attempt cleanup\n- preserves bundle MCP and CLI live-session cleanup for one-shot gateway CLI runs\n\n## Validation\n- `pnpm test src/agents/embedded-agent-runner.e2e.test.ts extensions/codex/src/app-server/run-attempt.test.ts src/commands/agent-via-gateway.test.ts src/gateway/server-methods/agent.test.ts src/agents/command/attempt-execution.cli.test.ts src/agents/cli-runner.before-agent-reply-cron.test.ts packages/gateway-protocol/src/schema/agent.test.ts`\n- `pnpm build`\n- `node scripts/lib/plugin-npm-runtime-build.mjs extensions/codex`\n- `node scripts/check-openclaw-package-tarball.mjs /tmp/openclaw-teardown-fix-package/openclaw-2026.6.2.tgz`\n\n## Live smoke\nValidated on `openclaw-vm01` with both the host OpenClaw runtime and managed `@openclaw/codex` plugin runtime deployed.\n\n- final session key: `agent:jarvis:teardown-source-aligned-smoke-20260609161031`\n- result: status `ok`, no embedded fallback, reply contained `gateway path ok`\n- cleanup log: `activeLeases=0 closed=true matchedSharedClient=true`\n- 25s post-run process check: no `codex app-server` or `agent-hub-proxy.ts` children remained\n\n## Operational note\nFor Codex harness fixes, validating only the host OpenClaw package is insufficient when a managed `@openclaw/codex` plugin install is active. The managed plugin runtime must also be built/refreshed and verified.\n",
